['<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list from an array? - Javascript / ReactJS\n\nI have this code that gets data through axios : \ncomponentDidMount() { \n  axios({ method:\'get\', url:"https://api......." }) // call api here... } });}   // end component did mount function`enter image description herefrom reactjs docs https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/components-and-props#stat', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I get a list from an array? [PHP]\n\nI have this code that gets all my files with certain extensions into one folder called "files". Then it counts how many times each file has been downloaded so far using md5_file(). \n$dir="./download"; //directory where you want download data stored \n $ext=array("pdf","docx");//list extension here which are allowed for downloading  from server   \n foreach($', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I use a variable as an array key? PHP / MySQLi Prepared Statement Error - Notice Undefined Index : Array Key Value Not Found In Database Table Column Name! \n\nI am trying this code below but it keeps giving me error messages like "Notice undefined index". It says that my $key value does not exist when checking if its equal with any values from database table column names... \n$stmt->bind_param(\'sssd\', $_POST[\'', "<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I get a list with all possible combinations from two lists? Python3x2+numpy + scipy - numpy array as an argument for function call not working properly! Help me out here plz!!!!! :) \n\nI have been trying this problem since yesterday but couldn't find any solution yet :( \nThe question goes like that : Write code which will take n numbers each time where 'i', j are integers between [a..b] range", '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I use a variable as an argument for another function? Python Tkinter GUI App - Error message "NameError name \'var_name\'" appears when using it with other functions that require arguments passed through var names like self etc... \n\nI am trying out some simple python code but have run into this problem where i cannot pass variables from one method call within my class object which contains all methods related to gui app creation  to any others called inside them without', "<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I get a list from an array? - Javascript / Jquery\n\nI have this code that gets data via ajax call : \n$.ajax({ \n  url:'http://localhost', //the url you want to request json file with php script inside it, for example http:/www.example.com/?json=get_data&callbackname='myfunction';//this will be called when we click submit button. The parameter 'callbakc", '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list from my database? - Django Python3 MySQLdb error 1064 "You have an error..." Mysql Error Number \'1054\': Unknown column \'\'user_id\'\' In Field List when running python manage runserver command line tool for django project using mysql db backend with pymysql connector installed via pip install --upgrade https://github.com/PyMySQL/mysqlclient-python#install. \nI am trying this tutorial http', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list from an array? - Swift3 / Xcode8 Beta 5 iOS10 beta5 app development using swift language for ios 10+ devices only! \n\nI am trying out some code that will allow me access data stored within my coreData database into arrays so they are easier accessible later down the line when building up views etc... \nThe problem im facing at this point though it seems like its not working as expected.. Im getting errors with', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list with all files that have been modified today? - Windows Server 2008 R2 / Powershell v3+ \n\nI am trying to create an automated backup script for our servers using powershellel but need some help getting started... \nThe idea would be something like this : Get filelist from directory where date last updated was yesterday + current day, then copy those into another folder.  This way we only back up what has changed since', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I get a list from an array? - Swift 5 Xcode 11 Beta Version iOS 13 Simulator 12F69 MacOS 10.14 Mojave OSX Catalyst v12B55a beta version macosx64_appkit1061__sim___mac os x sierra publicbeta4 com.apple.dt.dbg.DebuggerUISimulationRemoteUI [11] Debugging with gdb --args /Applications/SimulatedMetrics', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I make a custom view with rounded corners? Android Studio / JavaFXPorts Library - FXML file not found exception error when running app from IntelliJ IDEa 14 Ultimate Edition for Mac OS X 10.10 Yosemite Beta 5 64bit version \n\nI am trying out this tutorial here http://www.javafxports.org/#!/getting_started \nand have been able so far successfully run it using Netbeans 8 but now that', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list from an array? - Javascript / ReactJS\n\nI\'m trying to create my own custom component for reactjs but i have some problems with getting data out off it\'s state... \nThis are all components that make up this "customComponent": \n  import * as PropTypes from \'prop-types\';\n// import { connect } from\'react-redux\', because we\'re not using redux here! :)!!!!!!', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>The present invention relates generally to a method for manufacturing an optical fiber preform using vapor deposition techniques such as plasma chemical vapour deposition (“PCVD”) processes which are well known within this art field from U.S Pat No 5,262,026 issued Nov 1993 entitled “Method For Manufacturing Optical Fiber Preforms” assigned to Lucent Technologies Inc., assignee hereinof”. The disclosure thereof being incorporated into reference thereto without limitation with respect its content herewith below described specifically hereinafter disclosed embodiments relate more particularly', '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I get a list from an array? - Javascript / Jquery Mob