['<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list with all my installed packages?\n\nI want something like this but for Ubuntu 14.04 LTS : \n$ dpkg --get-selections | grep -v deinstall \n abiword                                      deinstall                    noarch     text editor that uses GTK+2 interface library   \n acroread7                                        install                       x86_64      Adobe Reader XI software suite              \n adb                                             ', "<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I make a list from an array? Python3x - List Comprehension vs For Loop Issue! [Beginner]\n\nI am trying out some basic python code for my class assignment but it seems that when using 'list comprehension', there are issues with how many items will be returned as opposed if you use just simple loops like this one below... \ndef main(): \n   my_array=[] #create empty Array here  #this can also", "<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I use a custom font with Xcode? How can i add it as an asset for my app so that other apps will be able too see this new one? \n\nI have downloaded some fonts from dafont website but how should they get added into xCode project folder structure. \nAlso, what are all steps required if we want our application's textview  to display these newly installed assets?? Do you need any special code written inside viewDidLoad", "<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow do I get a list from an array? SwiftUI List with ForEach loop not working as expected - Xcode 11 beta 5 iOS 13 Beta 8 GM seed 9B5a2b6d3e9c7ff8daef6744ccbe98feaeafdd77 \n\nI am trying out some simple code using swiftui for my first time but it's giving me problems that i can't seem solve myself so far... \nThe problem", '<Final Answer>:<|endoftext|>Q:\n\nHow can I get a list with all files that are not part of any package?\n\nI want an overview over my installed packages but also have access for every file which isn\'t included into o